<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Unit on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/unit/</link><description>Recent content in Unit on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/unit/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Systemd Unit Not Found</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/systemd/not-found8/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/systemd/not-found8/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="systemd-unit-not-found"&gt;Systemd Unit Not Found&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A unit not found error means systemd cannot locate the service, socket, or timer file. The unit was either never installed, was removed, or its file is in a location systemd does not scan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The unit file was deleted or never created&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The unit file is in a non-standard directory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A typo in the unit name&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The unit was not properly installed with &lt;code&gt;systemctl enable&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="verify-the-unit-file-exists"&gt;Verify the Unit File Exists&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ls /etc/systemd/system/&amp;lt;service-name&amp;gt;.service
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ls /lib/systemd/system/&amp;lt;service-name&amp;gt;.service
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="reload-systemd-after-adding-unit-files"&gt;Reload systemd After Adding Unit Files&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo systemctl daemon-reload
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="create-the-unit-file"&gt;Create the Unit File&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ini" data-lang="ini"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# /etc/systemd/system/my-app.service&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;[Unit]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Description&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;My Application&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;[Service]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ExecStart&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;/usr/bin/my-app&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Restart&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;on-failure&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;[Install]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;WantedBy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;multi-user.target&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="enable-and-start"&gt;Enable and Start&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo systemctl daemon-reload
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo systemctl enable --now my-app
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="list-all-available-units"&gt;List All Available Units&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;systemctl list-unit-files | grep &amp;lt;partial-name&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Typo in service name&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo systemctl start my-app
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Failed to start my-app.service: Unit my-app.service not found.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Fix: check the exact unit name with systemctl list-unit-files&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Unit file not reloaded after creation&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo systemctl start custom-service
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Unit custom-service.service not found.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Fix: systemctl daemon-reload &amp;amp;&amp;amp; systemctl start custom-service&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/systemd/already-active/"&gt;Already Active&lt;/a&gt; — unit is already running&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/systemd/service-failed/"&gt;Service Failed&lt;/a&gt; — unit exists but failed to start&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>